                            <comment id="75646" author="cbeams" created="Thu, 9 Feb 2012 04:47:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Yannick,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You&apos;re in luck &amp;#8211; this issue is already fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-9031&quot; title=&quot;@ComponentScan with includeFilters on @Import-ed context does not work&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-9031&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-9031&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  You can try it out in 3.1.1.BUILD-SNAPSHOT, but also note that we&apos;ll release 3.1.1 quite shortly anyway.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See the resolution comment there for complete details on why this was occurring, if you&apos;re interested.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="78496" author="avaz" created="Sun, 6 May 2012 12:18:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Chris,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using version 3.1.1 but seems that this problem ain&apos;t really go away. See the case bellow:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My tests context config is class based:&lt;br/&gt;
@Configuration&lt;br/&gt;
@ComponentScan(value=&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;com.acme&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
               excludeFilters=&lt;/p&gt;
{@ComponentScan.Filter(value=NoteController.class, 
                                                     type= FilterType.ASSIGNABLE_TYPE )}
&lt;p&gt; )&lt;br/&gt;
public class AcmeTestConfig {&lt;br/&gt;
    //Mock objects&lt;br/&gt;
    @Bean&lt;br/&gt;
    public NoteController noteController() &lt;/p&gt;
{
        NoteController noteController = Mockito.mock( NoteController.class );
        return noteController;
    }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And two beans in the package &quot;com.acme.controller&quot;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Controller&lt;br/&gt;
@Transactional&lt;br/&gt;
public class TaskController {&lt;br/&gt;
    @Autowired&lt;br/&gt;
    private NoteController noteController;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Controller&lt;br/&gt;
public class NoteController {&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is if a use the package &quot;com.acme&quot; for the value of @ComponentScan the excludeFilter property doesn&apos;t work, the class NoteController is not excluded from de scan, but if a use &quot;com.acme.controller&quot; the excludeFilter work and the class NoteController is excluded from the scan. I suppose that the excludeFilter needs to work on both type of package declaration.&lt;br/&gt;
Is this correct? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="78497" author="cbeams" created="Sun, 6 May 2012 12:29:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Anderson,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please follow the instructions at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-framework-issues#readme&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-framework-issues#readme&lt;/a&gt; to submit a simple reproduction of this problem, and also open a new JIRA issue so that we don&apos;t lose track of this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
